The paper discusses a generative approach to question answering, which falls under the sub-category of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML). Specifically, the paper focuses on encoding questions and passages to generate answers, which involves techniques such as neural networks and attention mechanisms. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
